    "text": "Erdős Problem #1075: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. Let $r\\geq 3$. There exists $c_r>r^{-r}$ such that, for any $\\epsilon>0$, if $n$ is sufficiently large, the following holds.\n\nAny $r$-uniform hypergraph on $n$ vertices with at least $(1+\\epsilon)(n/r)^r$ many edges contains a subgraph on $m$ vertices with at least $c_rm^r$ edges, where $m=m(n)\\to \\infty$ as $n\\to \\infty$. Prize: no. Tags: hypergraphs.",
